  "root_text": {
    "iti50:0.1": "Itivuttaka 50 ",
    "iti50:0.2": "Tikanipāta ",
    "iti50:0.3": "Paṭhamavagga ",
    "iti50:0.4": "Mūlasutta ",
    "iti50:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti50:2.1": "“Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, akusalamūlāni. ",
    "iti50:2.2": "Katamāni tīṇi? ",
    "iti50:2.3": "Lobho akusalamūlaṁ, doso akusalamūlaṁ, moho akusalamūlaṁ—",
    "iti50:2.4": "imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi akusalamūlānī”ti. ",
    "iti50:2.5": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti50:2.6": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti50:3.1": "“Lobho doso ca moho ca, ",
    "iti50:3.2": "purisaṁ pāpacetasaṁ; ",
    "iti50:3.3": "Hiṁsanti attasambhūtā, ",
    "iti50:3.4": "tacasāraṁva samphalan”ti. ",
    "iti50:4.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti50:4.2": "Paṭhamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti50:0.1": "So It Was Said 50 ",
    "iti50:0.2": "The Book of the Threes ",
    "iti50:0.3": "Chapter One ",
    "iti50:0.4": "Roots ",
    "iti50:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti50:2.1": "“Mendicants, there are these three unskillful roots. ",
    "iti50:2.2": "What three? ",
    "iti50:2.3": "Greed, hate, and delusion. ",
    "iti50:2.4": "These are the three unskillful roots.” ",
    "iti50:2.5": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti50:2.6": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti50:3.1": "“When greed, hate, and delusion, ",
    "iti50:3.2": "have arisen inside oneself, ",
    "iti50:3.3": "they harm a person of wicked heart, ",
    "iti50:3.4": "as a bamboo is destroyed by its own fruit.” ",
    "iti50:4.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
